7. Summary
1. Concept Brief
A 2D top-down shooter game where the player controls a 
cannon to destroy enemy planes while avoiding falling 
bombs. The game speeds up with time, and players must 
maintain their energy level while aiming for a high score.
2. Game Theme
Genre : Arcade/Action
Language : C++
Target Audience : Game development enthusiasts , arcade 
fans.
3. Mechanics & Features
=> Planes fly from the left to right randomly drop bombs.
=> The players’s cannon can move sideways and shoot 
bullets upwards.
=>Destroying planes earns points.
=> A high score list is maintained.
=> Bombs decrease the player’s energy on impact
4. Player Interaction
=> Move left : Left arrow.
=> Move Right : Right Arrow.
=> Shoot : Up Arrow or Spacebar
=> The player enters their name at the beginning.
5. Energy System
=> The player has an energy bar(starting at 100%).
=> Each time a bomb hits the player, energy decreases by 
20%.
=> When the energy reaches 0%, the game ends.
=> The energy bar adds realism and smooth difficulty 
scaling compared to fixed lives.
6. Development Details
=> Language : C++
=> Graphics Library : SFML
=> Architecture : Object -Oriented Programming 
=> Key Classes : 
1. Game : Handles the main loop, events, rendering .
2. Player : Manages position, shooting, and energy
3.Enemy : Handles plane movement and bomb 
dropping .
4.Bullet , Bomb : Collision and rendering logic.
7. Summary
The Space Shooter game blends action and strategy with 
real – time energy management. Built using SFML and 
C++, it’s perfect for learning core game development 
concepts like event handling, object- oriented design, and 
visual feedback systems
